The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 31 January is 36,245 (4,195.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 26 January, there were 2,521 new confirmed cases (291.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 19 January, there were 3,716 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 32% (1,195 fewer cases).
